Tundra does not support floating point arithmetic directly, we need to conv
convert raw values into integers before performing subtraction operation. 

Here is the corrected version of your Tundra code that would return the exp
expected result (68):

```tundra
def normalize(raw) {
  return {
    price: parseNumber(raw.price),
    promoDiscount: parseNumber(raw.promoDiscount),
    memberDiscount: parseNumber(raw.memberDiscount)
  };
}

val raw = {
  price: "80",
  promoDiscount: "12",
  memberDiscount: "5"
};

var item = normalize(raw);
var final = item.price - item.promoDiscount - item.memberDiscount;
print(final);
```
